This paper discusses the use of altmetrics in scholarly communication and research evaluation, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also addresses issues related to data quality and dependencies, which are relevant to the categories of computers and society (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SOC).
